Mauritius to Build a 20-Billion Rupee Terminal, Le Matinal Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-09-05T12:21:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-05/mauritius-to-build-a-20-billion-rupee-terminal-le-matinal-says.html
Mauritius Ports Authority plans to
build a terminal that will require 20 billion rupees ($712
million) of investment, le Matinal reported, without saying
where it got the information.  About 60 hectares (148 acres) of sea will be reclaimed to
meet requirements for the three-phase project that will cater
for 2 millions cargo containers, the Port Louis-based newspaper
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
1933 or  gbell16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
